# BuildX project context

BuildX is a **ground-up Go reimplementation** of the [OneDev](https://github.com/theonedev/onedev) backend (Java), not a fork. Product and API compatibility guide the migration.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|---|---|
| `buildx-server/` | Go server (migrated from `references/onedev`) |
| `buildx-cli/` | Go CLI (migrated from `references/tod`, parity with tod) |
| `references/` | Read-only git submodules — upstream OneDev sources |
| `docs/` | Project documentation and migration progress |

## References are read-only

Never edit, format, or commit changes under `references/`. Use them only to read and compare when porting code. Implement all changes in `buildx-server/`, `buildx-cli/`, or repo-root `docs/`.
